        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:08PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1108 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles east of Brevard, or near Dupont State Forest, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Little River In Transylvania County, Horse Shoe, Penrose, Etowah,
Brevard, Laurel Park, Valley Hill, and Forge Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
western North Carolina.</instruction>
